1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
AI coding tools move quickly. OpsTruth checks what is actually true afterwards.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:15,000
It runs local checks first and keeps missing runtime inputs visible instead of pretending they passed.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Verified, warning, failure, skipped, and not verified are separate states.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:33,000
The evidence is reviewable, but sensitive values stay out of the output.

5
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:43,000
OpsTruth 0.2.0 adds stronger evidence paths without silently making production calls.

6
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:51,000
The tool reports proof gaps because a skipped check is not a pass.

7
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:56,000
OpsTruth is a compact proof layer for AI-assisted engineering work.
